README

This is a simulation consisting of a single bar magnet and a charged particle. 

Current Trajectory: 
Use Panda3D -> add in another particle -> make dipoles induced and interacting -> more particles -> add in particle collision


Next Steps:
- Add in Panda3D along with Matplotlib and Numpy (Matplotlib is incredibly slow in rendering) and prove Forward Euler
- Semi-Implicit Euler comparison: theory (article) and implementation (prove the differences by rendering in Panda3D and using Matplotlib plots to compare numerically)
- Learn about errors, ig?

Stuff to go over:
- derivation of vector dipole formula
- net field direction inconsistency
- why does B become None when you add in the singularity?

two month goal:
make a decent physically true MR fluid being influenced by a magnet via particles
and perhaps then get an AI to run over it and figure out what the relation is between magnetic field and viscosity of fluid flow
so that then we can stop making particles and use fully normal fluid sims that other people have already made, just with that correlation, hopefully easier?


